text=The Third Book of Moses:  Called Leviticus%0a%0a%0a1:1 And the LORD called unto Moses, and spake unto him out of the%0atabernacle of the congregation, saying, 1:2 Speak unto the children of%0aIsrael, and say unto them, If any man of you bring an offering unto%0athe LORD, ye shall bring your offering of the cattle, even of the%0aherd, and of the flock.%0a%0a1:3 If his offering be a burnt sacrifice of the herd, let him offer a%0amale without blemish: he shall offer it of his own voluntary will at%0athe door of the tabernacle of the congregation before the LORD.%0a%0a1:4 And he shall put his hand upon the head of the burnt offering; and%0ait shall be accepted for him to make atonement for him.%0a%0a1:5 And he shall kill the bullock before the LORD: and the priests,%0aAaron's sons, shall bring the blood, and sprinkle the blood round%0aabout upon the altar that is by the door of the tabernacle of the%0acongregation.%0a%0a1:6 And he shall flay the burnt offering, and cut it into his pieces.%0a%0a1:7 And the sons of Aaron the priest shall put fire upon the altar,%0aand lay the wood in order upon the fire: 1:8 And the priests, Aaron's%0asons, shall lay the parts, the head, and the fat, in order upon the%0awood that is on the fire which is upon the altar: 1:9 But his inwards%0aand his legs shall he wash in water: and the priest shall burn all on%0athe altar, to be a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a%0asweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a1:10 And if his offering be of the flocks, namely, of the sheep, or of%0athe goats, for a burnt sacrifice; he shall bring it a male without%0ablemish.%0a%0a1:11 And he shall kill it on the side of the altar northward before%0athe LORD: and the priests, Aaron's sons, shall sprinkle his blood%0around about upon the altar.%0a%0a1:12 And he shall cut it into his pieces, with his head and his fat:%0aand the priest shall lay them in order on the wood that is on the fire%0awhich is upon the altar: 1:13 But he shall wash the inwards and the%0alegs with water: and the priest shall bring it all, and burn it upon%0athe altar: it is a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a%0asweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a1:14 And if the burnt sacrifice for his offering to the LORD be of%0afowls, then he shall bring his offering of turtledoves, or of young%0apigeons.%0a%0a1:15 And the priest shall bring it unto the altar, and wring off his%0ahead, and burn it on the altar; and the blood thereof shall be wrung%0aout at the side of the altar: 1:16 And he shall pluck away his crop%0awith his feathers, and cast it beside the altar on the east part, by%0athe place of the ashes: 1:17 And he shall cleave it with the wings%0athereof, but shall not divide it asunder: and the priest shall burn it%0aupon the altar, upon the wood that is upon the fire: it is a burnt%0asacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a2:1 And when any will offer a meat offering unto the LORD, his%0aoffering shall be of fine flour; and he shall pour oil upon it, and%0aput frankincense thereon: 2:2 And he shall bring it to Aaron's sons%0athe priests: and he shall take thereout his handful of the flour%0athereof, and of the oil thereof, with all the frankincense thereof;%0aand the priest shall burn the memorial of it upon the altar, to be an%0aoffering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD: 2:3 And the%0aremnant of the meat offering shall be Aaron's and his sons': it is a%0athing most holy of the offerings of the LORD made by fire.%0a%0a2:4 And if thou bring an oblation of a meat offering baken in the%0aoven, it shall be unleavened cakes of fine flour mingled with oil, or%0aunleavened wafers anointed with oil.%0a%0a2:5 And if thy oblation be a meat offering baken in a pan, it shall be%0aof fine flour unleavened, mingled with oil.%0a%0a2:6 Thou shalt part it in pieces, and pour oil thereon: it is a meat%0aoffering.%0a%0a2:7 And if thy oblation be a meat offering baken in the fryingpan, it%0ashall be made of fine flour with oil.%0a%0a2:8 And thou shalt bring the meat offering that is made of these%0athings unto the LORD: and when it is presented unto the priest, he%0ashall bring it unto the altar.%0a%0a2:9 And the priest shall take from the meat offering a memorial%0athereof, and shall burn it upon the altar: it is an offering made by%0afire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a2:10 And that which is left of the meat offering shall be Aaron's and%0ahis sons': it is a thing most holy of the offerings of the LORD made%0aby fire.%0a%0a2:11 No meat offering, which ye shall bring unto the LORD, shall be%0amade with leaven: for ye shall burn no leaven, nor any honey, in any%0aoffering of the LORD made by fire.%0a%0a2:12 As for the oblation of the firstfruits, ye shall offer them unto%0athe LORD: but they shall not be burnt on the altar for a sweet savour.%0a%0a2:13 And every oblation of thy meat offering shalt thou season with%0asalt; neither shalt thou suffer the salt of the covenant of thy God to%0abe lacking from thy meat offering: with all thine offerings thou shalt%0aoffer salt.%0a%0a2:14 And if thou offer a meat offering of thy firstfruits unto the%0aLORD, thou shalt offer for the meat offering of thy firstfruits green%0aears of corn dried by the fire, even corn beaten out of full ears.%0a%0a2:15 And thou shalt put oil upon it, and lay frankincense thereon: it%0ais a meat offering.%0a%0a2:16 And the priest shall burn the memorial of it, part of the beaten%0acorn thereof, and part of the oil thereof, with all the frankincense%0athereof: it is an offering made by fire unto the LORD.%0a%0a3:1 And if his oblation be a sacrifice of peace offering, if he offer%0ait of the herd; whether it be a male or female, he shall offer it%0awithout blemish before the LORD.%0a%0a3:2 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of his offering, and kill%0ait at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation: and Aaron's sons%0athe priests shall sprinkle the blood upon the altar round about.%0a%0a3:3 And he shall offer of the sacrifice of the peace offering an%0aoffering made by fire unto the LORD; the fat that covereth the%0ainwards, and all the fat that is upon the inwards, 3:4 And the two%0akidneys, and the fat that is on them, which is by the flanks, and the%0acaul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away.%0a%0a3:5 And Aaron's sons shall burn it on the altar upon the burnt%0asacrifice, which is upon the wood that is on the fire: it is an%0aoffering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a3:6 And if his offering for a sacrifice of peace offering unto the%0aLORD be of the flock; male or female, he shall offer it without%0ablemish.%0a%0a3:7 If he offer a lamb for his offering, then shall he offer it before%0athe LORD.%0a%0a3:8 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of his offering, and kill%0ait before the tabernacle of the congregation: and Aaron's sons shall%0asprinkle the blood thereof round about upon the altar.%0a%0a3:9 And he shall offer of the sacrifice of the peace offering an%0aoffering made by fire unto the LORD; the fat thereof, and the whole%0arump, it shall he take off hard by the backbone; and the fat that%0acovereth the inwards, and all the fat that is upon the inwards, 3:10%0aAnd the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon them, which is by the%0aflanks, and the caul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he%0atake away.%0a%0a3:11 And the priest shall burn it upon the altar: it is the food of%0athe offering made by fire unto the LORD.%0a%0a3:12 And if his offering be a goat, then he shall offer it before the%0aLORD.%0a%0a3:13 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of it, and kill it before%0athe tabernacle of the congregation: and the sons of Aaron shall%0asprinkle the blood thereof upon the altar round about.%0a%0a3:14 And he shall offer thereof his offering, even an offering made by%0afire unto the LORD; the fat that covereth the inwards, and all the fat%0athat is upon the inwards, 3:15 And the two kidneys, and the fat that%0ais upon them, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver,%0awith the kidneys, it shall he take away.%0a%0a3:16 And the priest shall burn them upon the altar: it is the food of%0athe offering made by fire for a sweet savour: all the fat is the%0aLORD's.%0a%0a3:17 It shall be a perpetual statute for your generations throughout%0aall your dwellings, that ye eat neither fat nor blood.%0a%0a4:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 4:2 Speak unto the children%0aof Israel, saying, If a soul shall sin through ignorance against any%0aof the commandments of the LORD concerning things which ought not to%0abe done, and shall do against any of them: 4:3 If the priest that is%0aanointed do sin according to the sin of the people; then let him bring%0afor his sin, which he hath sinned, a young bullock without blemish%0aunto the LORD for a sin offering.%0a%0a4:4 And he shall bring the bullock unto the door of the tabernacle of%0athe congregation before the LORD; and shall lay his hand upon the%0abullock's head, and kill the bullock before the LORD.%0a%0a4:5 And the priest that is anointed shall take of the bullock's blood,%0aand bring it to the tabernacle of the congregation: 4:6 And the priest%0ashall dip his finger in the blood, and sprinkle of the blood seven%0atimes before the LORD, before the vail of the sanctuary.%0a%0a4:7 And the priest shall put some of the blood upon the horns of the%0aaltar of sweet incense before the LORD, which is in the tabernacle of%0athe congregation; and shall pour all the blood of the bullock at the%0abottom of the altar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the%0atabernacle of the congregation.%0a%0a4:8 And he shall take off from it all the fat of the bullock for the%0asin offering; the fat that covereth the inwards, and all the fat that%0ais upon the inwards, 4:9 And the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon%0athem, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver, with the%0akidneys, it shall he take away, 4:10 As it was taken off from the%0abullock of the sacrifice of peace offerings: and the priest shall burn%0athem upon the altar of the burnt offering.%0a%0a4:11 And the skin of the bullock, and all his flesh, with his head,%0aand with his legs, and his inwards, and his dung, 4:12 Even the whole%0abullock shall he carry forth without the camp unto a clean place,%0awhere the ashes are poured out, and burn him on the wood with fire:%0awhere the ashes are poured out shall he be burnt.%0a%0a4:13 And if the whole congregation of Israel sin through ignorance,%0aand the thing be hid from the eyes of the assembly, and they have done%0asomewhat against any of the commandments of the LORD concerning things%0awhich should not be done, and are guilty; 4:14 When the sin, which%0athey have sinned against it, is known, then the congregation shall%0aoffer a young bullock for the sin, and bring him before the tabernacle%0aof the congregation.%0a%0a4:15 And the elders of the congregation shall lay their hands upon the%0ahead of the bullock before the LORD: and the bullock shall be killed%0abefore the LORD.%0a%0a4:16 And the priest that is anointed shall bring of the bullock's%0ablood to the tabernacle of the congregation: 4:17 And the priest shall%0adip his finger in some of the blood, and sprinkle it seven times%0abefore the LORD, even before the vail.%0a%0a4:18 And he shall put some of the blood upon the horns of the altar%0awhich is before the LORD, that is in the tabernacle of the%0acongregation, and shall pour out all the blood at the bottom of the%0aaltar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the tabernacle of%0athe congregation.%0a%0a4:19 And he shall take all his fat from him, and burn it upon the%0aaltar.%0a%0a4:20 And he shall do with the bullock as he did with the bullock for a%0asin offering, so shall he do with this: and the priest shall make an%0aatonement for them, and it shall be forgiven them.%0a%0a4:21 And he shall carry forth the bullock without the camp, and burn%0ahim as he burned the first bullock: it is a sin offering for the%0acongregation.%0a%0a4:22 When a ruler hath sinned, and done somewhat through ignorance%0aagainst any of the commandments of the LORD his God concerning things%0awhich should not be done, and is guilty; 4:23 Or if his sin, wherein%0ahe hath sinned, come to his knowledge; he shall bring his offering, a%0akid of the goats, a male without blemish: 4:24 And he shall lay his%0ahand upon the head of the goat, and kill it in the place where they%0akill the burnt offering before the LORD: it is a sin offering.%0a%0a4:25 And the priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering with%0ahis finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering,%0aand shall pour out his blood at the bottom of the altar of burnt%0aoffering.%0a%0a4:26 And he shall burn all his fat upon the altar, as the fat of the%0asacrifice of peace offerings: and the priest shall make an atonement%0afor him as concerning his sin, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a4:27 And if any one of the common people sin through ignorance, while%0ahe doeth somewhat against any of the commandments of the LORD%0aconcerning things which ought not to be done, and be guilty; 4:28 Or%0aif his sin, which he hath sinned, come to his knowledge: then he shall%0abring his offering, a kid of the goats, a female without blemish, for%0ahis sin which he hath sinned.%0a%0a4:29 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of the sin offering, and%0aslay the sin offering in the place of the burnt offering.%0a%0a4:30 And the priest shall take of the blood thereof with his finger,%0aand put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and shall%0apour out all the blood thereof at the bottom of the altar.%0a%0a4:31 And he shall take away all the fat thereof, as the fat is taken%0aaway from off the sacrifice of peace offerings; and the priest shall%0aburn it upon the altar for a sweet savour unto the LORD; and the%0apriest shall make an atonement for him, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a4:32 And if he bring a lamb for a sin offering, he shall bring it a%0afemale without blemish.%0a%0a4:33 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of the sin offering, and%0aslay it for a sin offering in the place where they kill the burnt%0aoffering.%0a%0a4:34 And the priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering with%0ahis finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering,%0aand shall pour out all the blood thereof at the bottom of the altar:%0a4:35 And he shall take away all the fat thereof, as the fat of the%0alamb is taken away from the sacrifice of the peace offerings; and the%0apriest shall burn them upon the altar, according to the offerings made%0aby fire unto the LORD: and the priest shall make an atonement for his%0asin that he hath committed, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a5:1 And if a soul sin, and hear the voice of swearing, and is a%0awitness, whether he hath seen or known of it; if he do not utter it,%0athen he shall bear his iniquity.%0a%0a5:2 Or if a soul touch any unclean thing, whether it be a carcase of%0aan unclean beast, or a carcase of unclean cattle, or the carcase of%0aunclean creeping things, and if it be hidden from him; he also shall%0abe unclean, and guilty.%0a%0a5:3 Or if he touch the uncleanness of man, whatsoever uncleanness it%0abe that a man shall be defiled withal, and it be hid from him; when he%0aknoweth of it, then he shall be guilty.%0a%0a5:4 Or if a soul swear, pronouncing with his lips to do evil, or to do%0agood, whatsoever it be that a man shall pronounce with an oath, and it%0abe hid from him; when he knoweth of it, then he shall be guilty in one%0aof these.%0a%0a5:5 And it shall be, when he shall be guilty in one of these things,%0athat he shall confess that he hath sinned in that thing: 5:6 And he%0ashall bring his trespass offering unto the LORD for his sin which he%0ahath sinned, a female from the flock, a lamb or a kid of the goats,%0afor a sin offering; and the priest shall make an atonement for him%0aconcerning his sin.%0a%0a5:7 And if he be not able to bring a lamb, then he shall bring for his%0atrespass, which he hath committed, two turtledoves, or two young%0apigeons, unto the LORD; one for a sin offering, and the other for a%0aburnt offering.%0a%0a5:8 And he shall bring them unto the priest, who shall offer that%0awhich is for the sin offering first, and wring off his head from his%0aneck, but shall not divide it asunder: 5:9 And he shall sprinkle of%0athe blood of the sin offering upon the side of the altar; and the rest%0aof the blood shall be wrung out at the bottom of the altar: it is a%0asin offering.%0a%0a5:10 And he shall offer the second for a burnt offering, according to%0athe manner: and the priest shall make an atonement for him for his sin%0awhich he hath sinned, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a5:11 But if he be not able to bring two turtledoves, or two young%0apigeons, then he that sinned shall bring for his offering the tenth%0apart of an ephah of fine flour for a sin offering; he shall put no oil%0aupon it, neither shall he put any frankincense thereon: for it is a%0asin offering.%0a%0a5:12 Then shall he bring it to the priest, and the priest shall take%0ahis handful of it, even a memorial thereof, and burn it on the altar,%0aaccording to the offerings made by fire unto the LORD: it is a sin%0aoffering.%0a%0a5:13 And the priest shall make an atonement for him as touching his%0asin that he hath sinned in one of these, and it shall be forgiven him:%0aand the remnant shall be the priest's, as a meat offering.%0a%0a5:14 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 5:15 If a soul commit a%0atrespass, and sin through ignorance, in the holy things of the LORD;%0athen he shall bring for his trespass unto the LORD a ram without%0ablemish out of the flocks, with thy estimation by shekels of silver,%0aafter the shekel of the sanctuary, for a trespass offering.%0a%0a5:16 And he shall make amends for the harm that he hath done in the%0aholy thing, and shall add the fifth part thereto, and give it unto the%0apriest: and the priest shall make an atonement for him with the ram of%0athe trespass offering, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a5:17 And if a soul sin, and commit any of these things which are%0aforbidden to be done by the commandments of the LORD; though he wist%0ait not, yet is he guilty, and shall bear his iniquity.%0a%0a5:18 And he shall bring a ram without blemish out of the flock, with%0athy estimation, for a trespass offering, unto the priest: and the%0apriest shall make an atonement for him concerning his ignorance%0awherein he erred and wist it not, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%0a5:19 It is a trespass offering: he hath certainly trespassed against%0athe LORD.%0a%0a6:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 6:2 If a soul sin, and%0acommit a trespass against the LORD, and lie unto his neighbour in that%0awhich was delivered him to keep, or in fellowship, or in a thing taken%0aaway by violence, or hath deceived his neighbour; 6:3 Or have found%0athat which was lost, and lieth concerning it, and sweareth falsely; in%0aany of all these that a man doeth, sinning therein: 6:4 Then it shall%0abe, because he hath sinned, and is guilty, that he shall restore that%0awhich he took violently away, or the thing which he hath deceitfully%0agotten, or that which was delivered him to keep, or the lost thing%0awhich he found, 6:5 Or all that about which he hath sworn falsely; he%0ashall even restore it in the principal, and shall add the fifth part%0amore thereto, and give it unto him to whom it appertaineth, in the day%0aof his trespass offering.%0a%0a6:6 And he shall bring his trespass offering unto the LORD, a ram%0awithout blemish out of the flock, with thy estimation, for a trespass%0aoffering, unto the priest: 6:7 And the priest shall make an atonement%0afor him before the LORD: and it shall be forgiven him for any thing of%0aall that he hath done in trespassing therein.%0a%0a6:8 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 6:9 Command Aaron and his%0asons, saying, This is the law of the burnt offering: It is the burnt%0aoffering, because of the burning upon the altar all night unto the%0amorning, and the fire of the altar shall be burning in it.%0a%0a6:10 And the priest shall put on his linen garment, and his linen%0abreeches shall he put upon his flesh, and take up the ashes which the%0afire hath consumed with the burnt offering on the altar, and he shall%0aput them beside the altar.%0a%0a6:11 And he shall put off his garments, and put on other garments, and%0acarry forth the ashes without the camp unto a clean place.%0a%0a6:12 And the fire upon the altar shall be burning in it; it shall not%0abe put out: and the priest shall burn wood on it every morning, and%0alay the burnt offering in order upon it; and he shall burn thereon the%0afat of the peace offerings.%0a%0a6:13 The fire shall ever be burning upon the altar; it shall never go%0aout.%0a%0a6:14 And this is the law of the meat offering: the sons of Aaron shall%0aoffer it before the LORD, before the altar.%0a%0a6:15 And he shall take of it his handful, of the flour of the meat%0aoffering, and of the oil thereof, and all the frankincense which is%0aupon the meat offering, and shall burn it upon the altar for a sweet%0asavour, even the memorial of it, unto the LORD.%0a%0a6:16 And the remainder thereof shall Aaron and his sons eat: with%0aunleavened bread shall it be eaten in the holy place; in the court of%0athe tabernacle of the congregation they shall eat it.%0a%0a6:17 It shall not be baken with leaven. I have given it unto them for%0atheir portion of my offerings made by fire; it is most holy, as is the%0asin offering, and as the trespass offering.%0a%0a6:18 All the males among the children of Aaron shall eat of it. It%0ashall be a statute for ever in your generations concerning the%0aofferings of the LORD made by fire: every one that toucheth them shall%0abe holy.%0a%0a6:19 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 6:20 This is the offering%0aof Aaron and of his sons, which they shall offer unto the LORD in the%0aday when he is anointed; the tenth part of an ephah of fine flour for%0aa meat offering perpetual, half of it in the morning, and half thereof%0aat night.%0a%0a6:21 In a pan it shall be made with oil; and when it is baken, thou%0ashalt bring it in: and the baken pieces of the meat offering shalt%0athou offer for a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%0a6:22 And the priest of his sons that is anointed in his stead shall%0aoffer it: it is a statute for ever unto the LORD; it shall be wholly%0aburnt.%0a%0a6:23 For every meat offering for the priest shall be wholly burnt: it%0ashall not be eaten.%0a%0a6:24 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 6:25 Speak unto Aaron and%0ato his sons, saying, This is the law of the sin offering: In the place%0awhere the burnt offering is killed shall the sin offering be killed%0abefore the LORD: it is most holy.%0a%0a6:26 The priest that offereth it for sin shall eat it: in the holy%0aplace shall it be eaten, in the court of the tabernacle of the%0acongregation.%0a%0a6:27 Whatsoever shall touch the flesh thereof shall be holy: and when%0athere is sprinkled of the blood thereof upon any garment, thou shalt%0awash that whereon it was sprinkled in the holy place.%0a%0a6:28 But the earthen vessel wherein it is sodden shall be broken: and%0aif it be sodden in a brasen pot, it shall be both scoured, and rinsed%0ain water.%0a%0a6:29 All the males among the priests shall eat thereof: it is most%0aholy.%0a%0a6:30 And no sin offering, whereof any of the blood is brought into the%0atabernacle of the congregation to reconcile withal in the holy place,%0ashall be eaten: it shall be burnt in the fire.%0a%0a7:1 Likewise this is the law of the trespass offering: it is most%0aholy.%0a%0a7:2 In the place where they kill the burnt offering shall they kill%0athe trespass offering: and the blood thereof shall he sprinkle round%0aabout upon the altar.%0a%0a7:3 And he shall offer of it all the fat thereof; the rump, and the%0afat that covereth the inwards, 7:4 And the two kidneys, and the fat%0athat is on them, which is by the flanks, and the caul that is above%0athe liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away: 7:5 And the priest%0ashall burn them upon the altar for an offering made by fire unto the%0aLORD: it is a trespass offering.%0a%0a7:6 Every male among the priests shall eat thereof: it shall be eaten%0ain the holy place: it is most holy.%0a%0a7:7 As the sin offering is, so is the trespass offering: there is one%0alaw for them: the priest that maketh atonement therewith shall have%0ait.%0a%0a7:8 And the priest that offereth any man's burnt offering, even the%0apriest shall have to himself the skin of the burnt offering which he%0ahath offered.%0a%0a7:9 And all the meat offering that is baken in the oven, and all that%0ais dressed in the fryingpan, and in the pan, shall be the priest's%0athat offereth it.%0a%0a7:10 And every meat offering, mingled with oil, and dry, shall all the%0asons of Aaron have, one as much as another.%0a%0a7:11 And this is the law of the sacrifice of peace offerings, which he%0ashall offer unto the LORD.%0a%0a7:12 If he offer it for a thanksgiving, then he shall offer with the%0asacrifice of thanksgiving unleavened cakes mingled with oil, and%0aunleavened wafers anointed with oil, and cakes mingled with oil, of%0afine flour, fried.%0a%0a7:13 Besides the cakes, he shall offer for his offering leavened bread%0awith the sacrifice of thanksgiving of his peace offerings.%0a%0a7:14 And of it he shall offer one out of the whole oblation for an%0aheave offering unto the LORD, and it shall be the priest's that%0asprinkleth the blood of the peace offerings.%0a%0a7:15 And the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offerings for%0athanksgiving shall be eaten the same day that it is offered; he shall%0anot leave any of it until the morning.%0a%0a7:16 But if the sacrific