t%0aoffering, and a young pigeon, or a turtledove, for a sin offering,%0aunto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, unto the priest:%0a12:7 Who shall offer it before the LORD, and make an atonement for%0aher; and she shall be cleansed from the issue of her blood. This is%0athe law for her that hath born a male or a female.%0a%0a12:8 And if she be not able to bring a lamb, then she shall bring two%0aturtles, or two young pigeons; the one for the burnt offering, and the%0aother for a sin offering: and the priest shall make an atonement for%0aher, and she shall be clean.%0a%0a13:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron, saying, 13:2 When a man%0ashall have in the skin of his flesh a rising, a scab, or bright spot,%0aand it be in the skin of his flesh like the plague of leprosy; then he%0ashall be brought unto Aaron the priest, or unto one of his sons the%0apriests: 13:3 And the priest shall look on the plague in the skin of%0athe flesh: and when the hair in the plague is turned white, and the%0aplague in sight be deeper than the skin of his flesh, it is a plague%0aof leprosy: and the priest shall look on him, and pronounce him%0aunclean.%0a%0a13:4 If the bright spot be white in the skin of his flesh, and in%0asight be not deeper than the skin, and the hair thereof be not turned%0awhite; then the priest shall shut up him that hath the plague seven%0adays: 13:5 And the priest shall look on him the seventh day: and,%0abehold, if the plague in his sight be at a stay, and the plague spread%0anot in the skin; then the priest shall shut him up seven days more:%0a13:6 And the priest shall look on him again the seventh day: and,%0abehold, if the plague be somewhat dark, and the plague spread not in%0athe skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean: it is but a scab: and%0ahe shall wash his clothes, and be clean.%0a%0a13:7 But if the scab spread much abroad in the skin, after that he%0ahath been seen of the priest for his cleansing, he shall be seen of%0athe priest aga