adark; then the priest shall shut him up seven days: 13:22 And if it%0aspread much abroad in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him%0aunclean: it is a plague.%0a%0a13:23 But if the bright spot stay in his place, and spread not, it is%0aa burning boil; and the priest shall pronounce him clean.%0a%0a13:24 Or if there be any flesh, in the skin whereof there is a hot%0aburning, and the quick flesh that burneth have a white bright spot,%0asomewhat reddish, or white; 13:25 Then the priest shall look upon it:%0aand, behold, if the hair in the bright spot be turned white, and it be%0ain sight deeper than the skin; it is a leprosy broken out of the%0aburning: wherefore the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is the%0aplague of leprosy.%0a%0a13:26 But if the priest look on it, and, behold, there be no white%0ahair in the bright spot, and it be no lower than the other skin, but%0abe somewhat dark; then the priest shall shut him up seven days: 13:27%0aAnd the priest shall look upon him the seventh day: and if it be%0aspread much abroad in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him%0aunclean: it is the plague of leprosy.%0a%0a13:28 And if the bright spot stay in his place, and spread not in the%0askin, but it be somewhat dark; it is a rising of the burning, and the%0apriest shall pronounce him clean: for it is an inflammation of the%0aburning.%0a%0a13:29 If a man or woman have a plague upon the head or the beard;%0a13:30 Then the priest shall see the plague: and, behold, if it be in%0asight deeper than the skin; and there be in it a yellow thin hair;%0athen the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a dry scall, even a%0aleprosy upon the head or beard.%0a%0a13:31 And if the priest look on the plague of the scall, and, behold,%0ait be not in sight deeper than the skin, and that there is no black%0ahair in it; then the priest shall shut up him that hath the plague of%0athe scall seven days: 13:32 And in the seventh day the priest shall%0alook on the plague: and, behold, if the scall spread not, and there be%0ain it no yellow hair, and the scall be not in sight deeper than the%0askin; 13:33 He shall be shaven, but the scall shall he not shave; and%0athe priest shall shut up him that hath the scall seven days more:%0a13:34 And in the seventh day the priest shall look on the scall: and,%0abehold, if the scall be not spread in the skin, nor be in sight deeper%0athan the skin; then the priest shall pronounce him clean: and he shall%0awash his clothes, and be clean.%0a%0a13:35 But if the scall spread much in the skin after his cleansing;%0a13:36 Then the priest shall look on him: and, behold, if the scall be%0aspread in the skin, the priest shall not seek for yellow hair; he is%0aunclean.%0a%0a13:37 But if the scall be in his sight at a stay, and that there is%0ablack hair grown up therein; the scall is healed, he is clean: and the%0apriest shall pronounce him clean.%0a%0a13:38 If a man also or a woman have in the skin of their flesh bright%0aspots, even white bright spots; 13:39 Then the priest shall look: and,%0abehold, if the bright spots in the skin of their flesh be darkish%0awhite; it is a freckled spot that groweth in the skin; he is clean.%0a%0a13:40 And the man whose hair is fallen off his head, he is bald; yet%0ais he clean.%0a%0a13:41 And he that hath his hair fallen off from the part of his head%0atoward his face, he is forehead bald: yet is he clean.%0a%0a13:42 And if there be in the bald head, or bald forehead, a white%0areddish sore; it is a leprosy sprung up in his bald head, or his bald%0aforehead.%0a%0a13:43 Then the priest shall look upon it: and, behold, if the rising%0aof the sore be white reddish in his bald head, or in his bald%0aforehead, as the leprosy appeareth in the skin of the flesh; 13:44 He%0ais a leprous man, he is unclean: the priest shall pronounce him%0autterly unclean; his plague is in his head.%0a%0a13:45 And the leper in whom the plague is, his clothes shall be rent,%0aand his head bare, and he