 And if%0ait appear still in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or%0ain any thing of skin; it is a spreading plague: thou shalt burn that%0awherein the plague is with fire.%0a%0a13:58 And the garment, either warp, or woof, or whatsoever thing of%0askin it be, which thou shalt wash, if the plague be departed from%0athem, then it shall be washed the second time, and shall be clean.%0a%0a13:59 This is the law of the plague of leprosy in a garment of woollen%0aor linen, either in the warp, or woof, or any thing of skins, to%0apronounce it clean, or to pronounce it unclean.%0a%0a14:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 14:2 This shall be the law%0aof the leper in the day of his cleansing: He shall be brought unto the%0apriest: 14:3 And the priest shall go forth out of the camp; and the%0apriest shall look, and, behold, if the plague of leprosy be healed in%0athe leper; 14:4 Then shall the priest command to take for him that is%0ato be cleansed two birds alive and clean, and cedar wood, and scarlet,%0aand hyssop: 14:5 And the priest shall command that one of the birds be%0akilled in an earthen vessel over running water: 14:6 As for the living%0abird, he shall take it, and the cedar wood, and the scarlet, and the%0ahyssop, and shall dip them and the living bird in the blood of the%0abird that was killed over the running water: 14:7 And he shall%0asprinkle upon him that is to be cleansed from the leprosy seven times,%0aand shall pronounce him clean, and shall let the living bird loose%0ainto the open field.%0a%0a14:8 And he that is to be cleansed shall wash his clothes, and shave%0aoff all his hair, and wash himself in water, that he may be clean: and%0aafter that he shall come into the camp, and shall tarry abroad out of%0ahis tent seven days.%0a%0a14:9 But it shall be on the seventh day, that he shall shave all his%0ahair off his head and his beard and his eyebrows, even all his hair he%0ashall shave off: and he shall wash his clothes, also he shall wash 