ther for a burnt offering, with the%0ameat offering: and the priest shall make an atonement for him that is%0ato be cleansed before the LORD.%0a%0a14:32 This is the law of him in whom is the plague of leprosy, whose%0ahand is not able to get that which pertaineth to his cleansing.%0a%0a14:33 And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying, 14:34 When%0aye be come into the land of Canaan, which I give to you for a%0apossession, and I put the plague of leprosy in a house of the land of%0ayour possession; 14:35 And he that owneth the house shall come and%0atell the priest, saying, It seemeth to me there is as it were a plague%0ain the house: 14:36 Then the priest shall command that they empty the%0ahouse, before the priest go into it to see the plague, that all that%0ais in the house be not made unclean: and afterward the priest shall go%0ain to see the house: 14:37 And he shall look on the plague, and,%0abehold, if the plague be in the walls of the house with hollow%0astrakes, greenish or reddish, which in sight are lower than the wall;%0a14:38 Then the priest shall go out of the house to the door of the%0ahouse, and shut up the house seven days: 14:39 And the priest shall%0acome again the seventh day, and shall look: and, behold, if the plague%0abe spread in the walls of the house; 14:40 Then the priest shall%0acommand that they take away the stones in which the plague is, and%0athey shall cast them into an unclean place without the city: 14:41 And%0ahe shall cause the house to be scraped within round about, and they%0ashall pour out the dust that they scrape off without the city into an%0aunclean place: 14:42 And they shall take other stones, and put them in%0athe place of those stones; and he shall take other morter, and shall%0aplaister the house.%0a%0a14:43 And if the plague come again, and break out in the house, after%0athat he hath taken away the stones, and after he hath scraped the%0ahouse, and after it is plaistered; 14:44 Then the priest shall come%0a