sue he is unclean.%0a%0a15:3 And this shall be his uncleanness in his issue: whether his flesh%0arun with his issue, or his flesh be stopped from his issue, it is his%0auncleanness.%0a%0a15:4 Every bed, whereon he lieth that hath the issue, is unclean: and%0aevery thing, whereon he sitteth, shall be unclean.%0a%0a15:5 And whosoever toucheth his bed shall wash his clothes, and bathe%0ahimself in water, and be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:6 And he that sitteth on any thing whereon he sat that hath the%0aissue shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be%0aunclean until the even.%0a%0a15:7 And he that toucheth the flesh of him that hath the issue shall%0awash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the%0aeven.%0a%0a15:8 And if he that hath the issue spit upon him that is clean; then%0ahe shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean%0auntil the even.%0a%0a15:9 And what saddle soever he rideth upon that hath the issue shall%0abe unclean.%0a%0a15:10 And whosoever toucheth any thing that was under him shall be%0aunclean until the even: and he that beareth any of those things shall%0awash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the%0aeven.%0a%0a15:11 And whomsoever he toucheth that hath the issue, and hath not%0arinsed his hands in water, he shall wash his clothes, and bathe%0ahimself in water, and be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:12 And the vessel of earth, that he toucheth which hath the issue,%0ashall be broken: and every vessel of wood shall be rinsed in water.%0a%0a15:13 And when he that hath an issue is cleansed of his issue; then he%0ashall number to himself seven days for his cleansing, and wash his%0aclothes, and bathe his flesh in running water, and shall be clean.%0a%0a15:14 And on the eighth day he shall take to him two turtledoves, or%0atwo young pigeons, and come before the LORD unto the door of the%0atabernacle of the congregation, and give them unto the priest: 15:15%0aAnd the priest shall offer them, the one for a sin offering, and the%0aother for a burnt offering; and the priest shall make an atonement for%0ahim before the LORD for his issue.%0a%0a15:16 And if any man's seed of copulation go out from him, then he%0ashall wash all his flesh in water, and be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:17 And every garment, and every skin, whereon is the seed of%0acopulation, shall be washed with water, and be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:18 The woman also with whom man shall lie with seed of copulation,%0athey shall both bathe themselves in water, and be unclean until the%0aeven.%0a%0a15:19 And if a woman have an issue, and her issue in her flesh be%0ablood, she shall be put apart seven days: and whosoever toucheth her%0ashall be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:20 And every thing that she lieth upon in her separation shall be%0aunclean: every thing also that she sitteth upon shall be unclean.%0a%0a15:21 And whosoever toucheth her bed shall wash his clothes, and bathe%0ahimself in water, and be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:22 And whosoever toucheth any thing that she sat upon shall wash%0ahis clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the%0aeven.%0a%0a15:23 And if it be on her bed, or on any thing whereon she sitteth,%0awhen he toucheth it, he shall be unclean until the even.%0a%0a15:24 And if any man lie with her at all, and her flowers be upon him,%0ahe shall be unclean seven days; and all the bed whereon he lieth shall%0abe unclean.%0a%0a15:25 And if a woman have an issue of her blood many days out of the%0atime of her separation, or if it run beyond the time of her%0aseparation; all the days of the issue of her uncleanness shall be as%0athe days of her separation: she shall be unclean.%0a%0a15:26 Every bed whereon she lieth all the days of her issue shall be%0aunto her as the bed of her separation: and whatsoever she sitteth upon%0ashall be unclean, as the uncleanness of her separation.%0a%0a15:27 And whosoever toucheth those things shall be unclean, and shall%0awash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the%0aeven.%0a%0a15:28 But if she be cleansed of her issue, then she shall number to%0aherself seven days, and after that she shall be clean.%0a%0a15:29 And on the eighth day she shall take unto her two turtles, or%0atwo young pigeons, and bring them unto the priest, to the door of the%0atabernacle of the congregation.%0a%0a15:30 And the priest shall offer the one for a sin offering, and the%0aother for a burnt offering; and the priest shall make an atonement for%0aher before the LORD for the issue of her uncleanness.%0a%0a15:31 Thus shall ye separate the children of Israel from their%0auncleanness; that they die not in their uncleanness, when they defile%0amy tabernacle that is among them.%0a%0a15:32 This is the law of him that hath an issue, and of him whose seed%0agoeth from him, and is defiled therewith; 15:33 And of her that is%0asick of her flowers, and of him that hath an issue, of the man, and of%0athe woman, and of him that lieth with her that is unclean.%0a%0a16:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses after the death of the two sons of%0aAaron, when they offered before the LORD, and died; 16:2 And the LORD%0asaid unto Moses, Speak unto Aaron thy brother, that he come not at all%0atimes into the holy place within the vail before the mercy seat, which%0ais upon the ark; that he die not: for I will appear in the cloud upon%0athe mercy seat.%0a%0a16:3 Thus shall Aaron come into the holy place: with a young bullock%0afor a sin offering, and a ram for a burnt offering.%0a%0a16:4 He shall put on the holy linen coat, and he shall have the linen%0abreeches upon his flesh, and shall be girded with a linen girdle, and%0awith the linen mitre shall he be attired: these are holy garments;%0atherefore shall he wash his flesh in water, and so put them on.%0a%0a16:5 And he shall take of the congregation of the children of Israel%0atwo kids of the goats for a sin offering, and