, that remaineth%0aamong them in the midst of their uncleanness.%0a%0a16:17 And there shall be no man in the tabernacle of the congregation%0awhen he goeth in to make an atonement in the holy place, until he come%0aout, and have made an atonement for himself, and for his household,%0aand for all the congregation of Israel.%0a%0a16:18 And he shall go out unto the altar that is before the LORD, and%0amake an atonement for it; and shall take of the blood of the bullock,%0aand of the blood of the goat, and put it upon the horns of the altar%0around about.%0a%0a16:19 And he shall sprinkle of the blood upon it with his finger seven%0atimes, and cleanse it, and hallow it from the uncleanness of the%0achildren of Israel.%0a%0a16:20 And when he hath made an end of reconciling the holy place, and%0athe tabernacle of the congregation, and the altar, he shall bring the%0alive goat: 16:21 And Aaron shall lay both his hands upon the head of%0athe live goat, and confess over him all the iniquities of the children%0aof Israel, and all their transgressions in all their sins, putting%0athem upon the head of the goat, and shall send him away by the hand of%0aa fit man into the wilderness: 16:22 And the goat shall bear upon him%0aall their iniquities unto a land not inhabited: and he shall let go%0athe goat in the wilderness.%0a%0a16:23 And Aaron shall come into the tabernacle of the congregation,%0aand shall put off the linen garments, which he put on when he went%0ainto the holy place, and shall leave them there: 16:24 And he shall%0awash his flesh with water in the holy place, and put on his garments,%0aand come forth, and offer his burnt offering, and the burnt offering%0aof the people, and make an atonement for himself, and for the people.%0a%0a16:25 And the fat of the sin offering shall he burn upon the altar.%0a%0a16:26 And he that let go the goat for the scapegoat shall wash his%0aclothes, and bathe his flesh in water, and afterward come into the%0acamp.%0a%0a16:27 And the bullock for the sin offering, and the goat for the sin%0aoffering, whose blood was brought in to make atonement in the holy%0aplace, shall one carry forth without the camp; and they shall burn in%0athe fire their skins, and their flesh, and their dung.%0a%0a16:28 And he that burneth them shall wash his clothes, and bathe his%0aflesh in water, and afterward he shall come into the camp.%0a%0a16:29 And this shall be a statute for ever unto you: that in the%0aseventh month, on the tenth day of the month, ye shall afflict your%0asouls, and do no work at all, whether it be one of your own country,%0aor a stranger that sojourneth among you: 16:30 For on that day shall%0athe priest make an atonement for you, to cleanse you, that ye may be%0aclean from all your sins before the LORD.%0a%0a16:31 It shall be a sabbath of rest unto you, and ye shall afflict%0ayour souls, by a statute for ever.%0a%0a16:32 And the priest, whom he shall anoint, and whom he shall%0aconsecrate to minister in the priest's office in his father's stead,%0ashall make the atonement, and shall put on the linen clothes, even the%0aholy garments: 16:33 And he shall make an atonement for the holy%0asanctuary, and he shall make an atonement for the tabernacle of the%0acongregation, and for the altar, and he shall make an atonement for%0athe priests, and for all the people of the congregation.%0a%0a16:34 And this shall be an everlasting statute unto you, to make an%0aatonement for the children of Israel for all their sins once a year.%0aAnd he did as the LORD commanded Moses.%0a%0a17:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 17:2 Speak unto Aaron, and%0aunto his sons, and unto all the children of Israel, and say unto them;%0aThis is the thing which the LORD hath commanded, saying, 17:3 What man%0asoever there be of the house of Israel, that killeth an ox, or lamb,%0aor goat, in the camp, or that killeth it out of the camp, 17:4 And%0abringeth it not unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation,%0ato offer an 