 daughter, begotten of thy%0afather, she is thy sister, thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.%0a%0a18:12 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father's sister: she%0ais thy father's near kinswoman.%0a%0a18:13 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy mother's sister: for%0ashe is thy mother's near kinswoman.%0a%0a18:14 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father's brother,%0athou shalt not approach to his wife: she is thine aunt.%0a%0a18:15 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy daughter in law: she%0ais thy son's wife; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.%0a%0a18:16 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy brother's wife: it%0ais thy brother's nakedness.%0a%0a18:17 Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her%0adaughter, neither shalt thou take her son's daughter, or her%0adaughter's daughter, to uncover her nakedness; for they are her near%0akinswomen: it is wickedness.%0a%0a18:18 Neither shalt thou take a wife to her sister, to vex her, to%0auncover her nakedness, beside the other in her life time.%0a%0a18:19 Also thou shalt not approach unto a woman to uncover her%0anakedness, as long as she is put apart for her uncleanness.%0a%0a18:20 Moreover thou shalt not lie carnally with thy neighbour's wife,%0ato defile thyself with her.%0a%0a18:21 And thou shalt not let any of thy seed pass through the fire to%0aMolech, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the LORD.%0a%0a18:22 Thou shalt not lie with mankind, as with womankind: it is%0aabomination.%0a%0a18:23 Neither shalt thou lie with any beast to defile thyself%0atherewith: neither shall any woman stand before a beast to lie down%0athereto: it is confusion.%0a%0a18:24 Defile not ye yourselves in any of these things: for in all%0athese the nations are defiled which I cast out before you: 18:25 And%0athe land is defiled: therefore I do visit the iniquity thereof upon%0ait, and the land itself vomiteth out her inhabitants.%0a%0a18:26 Ye shall therefore keep my statutes a