ch he hath%0abought, which is not of the fields of his possession; 27:23 Then the%0apriest shall reckon unto him the worth of thy estimation, even unto%0athe year of the jubile: and he shall give thine estimation in that%0aday, as a holy thing unto the LORD.%0a%0a27:24 In the year of the jubile the field shall return unto him of%0awhom it was bought, even to him to whom the possession of the land did%0abelong.%0a%0a27:25 And all thy estimations shall be according to the shekel of the%0asanctuary: twenty gerahs shall be the shekel.%0a%0a27:26 Only the firstling of the beasts, which should be the LORD's%0afirstling, no man shall sanctify it; whether it be ox, or sheep: it is%0athe LORD's.%0a%0a27:27 And if it be of an unclean beast, then he shall redeem it%0aaccording to thine estimation, and shall add a fifth part of it%0athereto: or if it be not redeemed, then it shall be sold according to%0athy estimation.%0a%0a27:28 Notwithstanding no devoted thing, that a man shall devote unto%0athe LORD of all that he hath, both of man and beast, and of the field%0aof his possession, shall be sold or redeemed: every devoted thing is%0amost holy unto the LORD.%0a%0a27:29 None devoted, which shall be devoted of men, shall be redeemed;%0abut shall surely be put to death.%0a%0a27:30 And all the tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land,%0aor of the fruit of the tree, is the LORD's: it is holy unto the LORD.%0a%0a27:31 And if a man will at all redeem ought of his tithes, he shall%0aadd thereto the fifth part thereof.%0a%0a27:32 And concerning the tithe of the herd, or of the flock, even of%0awhatsoever passeth under the rod, the tenth shall be holy unto the%0aLORD.%0a%0a27:33 He shall not search whether it be good or bad, neither shall he%0achange it: and if he change it at all, then both it and the change%0athereof shall be holy; it shall not be redeemed.%0a%0a27:34 These are the commandments, which the LORD commanded Moses for%0athe children of Israel in mount Sinai.%0a%0a
