diff:1678516998:1678516998:=1,2879d0%0a%3c The Third Book of Moses:  Called Leviticus%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c 1:1 And the LORD called unto Moses, and spake unto him out of the%0a%3c tabernacle of the congregation, saying, 1:2 Speak unto the children of%0a%3c Israel, and say unto them, If any man of you bring an offering unto%0a%3c the LORD, ye shall bring your offering of the cattle, even of the%0a%3c herd, and of the flock.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:3 If his offering be a burnt sacrifice of the herd, let him offer a%0a%3c male without blemish: he shall offer it of his own voluntary will at%0a%3c the door of the tabernacle of the congregation before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:4 And he shall put his hand upon the head of the burnt offering; and%0a%3c it shall be accepted for him to make atonement for him.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:5 And he shall kill the bullock before the LORD: and the priests,%0a%3c Aaron's sons, shall bring the blood, and sprinkle the blood round%0a%3c about upon the altar that is by the door of the tabernacle of the%0a%3c congregation.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:6 And he shall flay the burnt offering, and cut it into his pieces.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:7 And the sons of Aaron the priest shall put fire upon the altar,%0a%3c and lay the wood in order upon the fire: 1:8 And the priests, Aaron's%0a%3c sons, shall lay the parts, the head, and the fat, in order upon the%0a%3c wood that is on the fire which is upon the altar: 1:9 But his inwards%0a%3c and his legs shall he wash in water: and the priest shall burn all on%0a%3c the altar, to be a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a%0a%3c sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:10 And if his offering be of the flocks, namely, of the sheep, or of%0a%3c the goats, for a burnt sacrifice; he shall bring it a male without%0a%3c blemish.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:11 And he shall kill it on the side of the altar northward before%0a%3c the LORD: and the priests, Aaron's sons, shall sprinkle his blood%0a%3c round about upon the altar.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:12 And he shall cut it into his pieces, with his head and his fat:%0a%3c and the priest shall lay them in order on the wood that is on the fire%0a%3c which is upon the altar: 1:13 But he shall wash the inwards and the%0a%3c legs with water: and the priest shall bring it all, and burn it upon%0a%3c the altar: it is a burnt sacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a%0a%3c sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:14 And if the burnt sacrifice for his offering to the LORD be of%0a%3c fowls, then he shall bring his offering of turtledoves, or of young%0a%3c pigeons.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1:15 And the priest shall bring it unto the altar, and wring off his%0a%3c head, and burn it on the altar; and the blood thereof shall be wrung%0a%3c out at the side of the altar: 1:16 And he shall pluck away his crop%0a%3c with his feathers, and cast it beside the altar on the east part, by%0a%3c the place of the ashes: 1:17 And he shall cleave it with the wings%0a%3c thereof, but shall not divide it asunder: and the priest shall burn it%0a%3c upon the altar, upon the wood that is upon the fire: it is a burnt%0a%3c sacrifice, an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:1 And when any will offer a meat offering unto the LORD, his%0a%3c offering shall be of fine flour; and he shall pour oil upon it, and%0a%3c put frankincense thereon: 2:2 And he shall bring it to Aaron's sons%0a%3c the priests: and he shall take thereout his handful of the flour%0a%3c thereof, and of the oil thereof, with all the frankincense thereof;%0a%3c and the priest shall burn the memorial of it upon the altar, to be an%0a%3c offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD: 2:3 And the%0a%3c remnant of the meat offering shall be Aaron's and his sons': it is a%0a%3c thing most holy of the offerings of the LORD made by fire.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:4 And if thou bring an oblation of a meat offering baken in the%0a%3c oven, it shall be unleavened cakes of fine flour mingled with oil, or%0a%3c unleavened wafers anointed with oil.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:5 And if thy oblation be a meat offering baken in a pan, it shall be%0a%3c of fine flour unleavened, mingled with oil.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:6 Thou shalt part it in pieces, and pour oil thereon: it is a meat%0a%3c offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:7 And if thy oblation be a meat offering baken in the fryingpan, it%0a%3c shall be made of fine flour with oil.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:8 And thou shalt bring the meat offering that is made of these%0a%3c things unto the LORD: and when it is presented unto the priest, he%0a%3c shall bring it unto the altar.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:9 And the priest shall take from the meat offering a memorial%0a%3c thereof, and shall burn it upon the altar: it is an offering made by%0a%3c fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:10 And that which is left of the meat offering shall be Aaron's and%0a%3c his sons': it is a thing most holy of the offerings of the LORD made%0a%3c by fire.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:11 No meat offering, which ye shall bring unto the LORD, shall be%0a%3c made with leaven: for ye shall burn no leaven, nor any honey, in any%0a%3c offering of the LORD made by fire.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:12 As for the oblation of the firstfruits, ye shall offer them unto%0a%3c the LORD: but they shall not be burnt on the altar for a sweet savour.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:13 And every oblation of thy meat offering shalt thou season with%0a%3c salt; neither shalt thou suffer the salt of the covenant of thy God to%0a%3c be lacking from thy meat offering: with all thine offerings thou shalt%0a%3c offer salt.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:14 And if thou offer a meat offering of thy firstfruits unto the%0a%3c LORD, thou shalt offer for the meat offering of thy firstfruits green%0a%3c ears of corn dried by the fire, even corn beaten out of full ears.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:15 And thou shalt put oil upon it, and lay frankincense thereon: it%0a%3c is a meat offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 2:16 And the priest shall burn the memorial of it, part of the beaten%0a%3c corn thereof, and part of the oil thereof, with all the frankincense%0a%3c thereof: it is an offering made by fire unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:1 And if his oblation be a sacrifice of peace offering, if he offer%0a%3c it of the herd; whether it be a male or female, he shall offer it%0a%3c without blemish before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:2 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of his offering, and kill%0a%3c it at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation: and Aaron's sons%0a%3c the priests shall sprinkle the blood upon the altar round about.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:3 And he shall offer of the sacrifice of the peace offering an%0a%3c offering made by fire unto the LORD; the fat that covereth the%0a%3c inwards, and all the fat that is upon the inwards, 3:4 And the two%0a%3c kidneys, and the fat that is on them, which is by the flanks, and the%0a%3c caul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:5 And Aaron's sons shall burn it on the altar upon the burnt%0a%3c sacrifice, which is upon the wood that is on the fire: it is an%0a%3c offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:6 And if his offering for a sacrifice of peace offering unto the%0a%3c LORD be of the flock; male or female, he shall offer it without%0a%3c blemish.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:7 If he offer a lamb for his offering, then shall he offer it before%0a%3c the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:8 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of his offering, and kill%0a%3c it before the tabernacle of the congregation: and Aaron's sons shall%0a%3c sprinkle the blood thereof round about upon the altar.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:9 And he shall offer of the sacrifice of the peace offering an%0a%3c offering made by fire unto the LORD; the fat thereof, and the whole%0a%3c rump, it shall he take off hard by the backbone; and the fat that%0a%3c covereth the inwards, and all the fat that is upon the inwards, 3:10%0a%3c And the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon them, which is by the%0a%3c flanks, and the caul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he%0a%3c take away.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:11 And the priest shall burn it upon the altar: it is the food of%0a%3c the offering made by fire unto the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:12 And if his offering be a goat, then he shall offer it before the%0a%3c LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:13 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of it, and kill it before%0a%3c the tabernacle of the congregation: and the sons of Aaron shall%0a%3c sprinkle the blood thereof upon the altar round about.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:14 And he shall offer thereof his offering, even an offering made by%0a%3c fire unto the LORD; the fat that covereth the inwards, and all the fat%0a%3c that is upon the inwards, 3:15 And the two kidneys, and the fat that%0a%3c is upon them, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver,%0a%3c with the kidneys, it shall he take away.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:16 And the priest shall burn them upon the altar: it is the food of%0a%3c the offering made by fire for a sweet savour: all the fat is the%0a%3c LORD's.%0a%3c %0a%3c 3:17 It shall be a perpetual statute for your generations throughout%0a%3c all your dwellings, that ye eat neither fat nor blood.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 4:2 Speak unto the children%0a%3c of Israel, saying, If a soul shall sin through ignorance against any%0a%3c of the commandments of the LORD concerning things which ought not to%0a%3c be done, and shall do against any of them: 4:3 If the priest that is%0a%3c anointed do sin according to the sin of the people; then let him bring%0a%3c for his sin, which he hath sinned, a young bullock without blemish%0a%3c unto the LORD for a sin offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:4 And he shall bring the bullock unto the door of the tabernacle of%0a%3c the congregation before the LORD; and shall lay his hand upon the%0a%3c bullock's head, and kill the bullock before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:5 And the priest that is anointed shall take of the bullock's blood,%0a%3c and bring it to the tabernacle of the congregation: 4:6 And the priest%0a%3c shall dip his finger in the blood, and sprinkle of the blood seven%0a%3c times before the LORD, before the vail of the sanctuary.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:7 And the priest shall put some of the blood upon the horns of the%0a%3c altar of sweet incense before the LORD, which is in the tabernacle of%0a%3c the congregation; and shall pour all the blood of the bullock at the%0a%3c bottom of the altar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the%0a%3c tabernacle of the congregation.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:8 And he shall take off from it all the fat of the bullock for the%0a%3c sin offering; the fat that covereth the inwards, and all the fat that%0a%3c is upon the inwards, 4:9 And the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon%0a%3c them, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver, with the%0a%3c kidneys, it shall he take away, 4:10 As it was taken off from the%0a%3c bullock of the sacrifice of peace offerings: and the priest shall burn%0a%3c them upon the altar of the burnt offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:11 And the skin of the bullock, and all his flesh, with his head,%0a%3c and with his legs, and his inwards, and his dung, 4:12 Even the whole%0a%3c bullock shall he carry forth without the camp unto a clean place,%0a%3c where the ashes are poured out, and burn him on the wood with fire:%0a%3c where the ashes are poured out shall he be burnt.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:13 And if the whole congregation of Israel sin through ignorance,%0a%3c and the thing be hid from the eyes of the assembly, and they have done%0a%3c somewhat against any of the commandments of the LORD concerning things%0a%3c which should not be done, and are guilty; 4:14 When the sin, which%0a%3c they have sinned against it, is known, then the congregation shall%0a%3c offer a young bullock for the sin, and bring him before the tabernacle%0a%3c of the congregation.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:15 And the elders of the congregation shall lay their hands upon the%0a%3c head of the bullock before the LORD: and the bullock shall be killed%0a%3c before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:16 And the priest that is anointed shall bring of the bullock's%0a%3c blood to the tabernacle of the congregation: 4:17 And the priest shall%0a%3c dip his finger in some of the blood, and sprinkle it seven times%0a%3c before the LORD, even before the vail.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:18 And he shall put some of the blood upon the horns of the altar%0a%3c which is before the LORD, that is in the tabernacle of the%0a%3c congregation, and shall pour out all the blood at the bottom of the%0a%3c altar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the tabernacle of%0a%3c the congregation.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:19 And he shall take all his fat from him, and burn it upon the%0a%3c altar.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:20 And he shall do with the bullock as he did with the bullock for a%0a%3c sin offering, so shall he do with this: and the priest shall make an%0a%3c atonement for them, and it shall be forgiven them.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:21 And he shall carry forth the bullock without the camp, and burn%0a%3c him as he burned the first bullock: it is a sin offering for the%0a%3c congregation.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:22 When a ruler hath sinned, and done somewhat through ignorance%0a%3c against any of the commandments of the LORD his God concerning things%0a%3c which should not be done, and is guilty; 4:23 Or if his sin, wherein%0a%3c he hath sinned, come to his knowledge; he shall bring his offering, a%0a%3c kid of the goats, a male without blemish: 4:24 And he shall lay his%0a%3c hand upon the head of the goat, and kill it in the place where they%0a%3c kill the burnt offering before the LORD: it is a sin offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:25 And the priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering with%0a%3c his finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering,%0a%3c and shall pour out his blood at the bottom of the altar of burnt%0a%3c offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:26 And he shall burn all his fat upon the altar, as the fat of the%0a%3c sacrifice of peace offerings: and the priest shall make an atonement%0a%3c for him as concerning his sin, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:27 And if any one of the common people sin through ignorance, while%0a%3c he doeth somewhat against any of the commandments of the LORD%0a%3c concerning things which ought not to be done, and be guilty; 4:28 Or%0a%3c if his sin, which he hath sinned, come to his knowledge: then he shall%0a%3c bring his offering, a kid of the goats, a female without blemish, for%0a%3c his sin which he hath sinned.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:29 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of the sin offering, and%0a%3c slay the sin offering in the place of the burnt offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:30 And the priest shall take of the blood thereof with his finger,%0a%3c and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and shall%0a%3c pour out all the blood thereof at the bottom of the altar.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:31 And he shall take away all the fat thereof, as the fat is taken%0a%3c away from off the sacrifice of peace offerings; and the priest shall%0a%3c burn it upon the altar for a sweet savour unto the LORD; and the%0a%3c priest shall make an atonement for him, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:32 And if he bring a lamb for a sin offering, he shall bring it a%0a%3c female without blemish.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:33 And he shall lay his hand upon the head of the sin offering, and%0a%3c slay it for a sin offering in the place where they kill the burnt%0a%3c offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 4:34 And the priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering with%0a%3c his finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering,%0a%3c and shall pour out all the blood thereof at the bottom of the altar:%0a%3c 4:35 And he shall take away all the fat thereof, as the fat of the%0a%3c lamb is taken away from the sacrifice of the peace offerings; and the%0a%3c priest shall burn them upon the altar, according to the offerings made%0a%3c by fire unto the LORD: and the priest shall make an atonement for his%0a%3c sin that he hath committed, and it shall be forgiven him.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:1 And if a soul sin, and hear the voice of swearing, and is a%0a%3c witness, whether he hath seen or known of it; if he do not utter it,%0a%3c then he shall bear his iniquity.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:2 Or if a soul touch any unclean thing, whether it be a carcase of%0a%3c an unclean beast, or a carcase of unclean cattle, or the carcase of%0a%3c unclean creeping things, and if it be hidden from him; he also shall%0a%3c be unclean, and guilty.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:3 Or if he touch the uncleanness of man, whatsoever uncleanness it%0a%3c be that a man shall be defiled withal, and it be hid from him; when he%0a%3c knoweth of it, then he shall be guilty.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:4 Or if a soul swear, pronouncing with his lips to do evil, or to do%0a%3c good, whatsoever it be that a man shall pronounce with an oath, and it%0a%3c be hid from him; when he knoweth of it, then he shall be guilty in one%0a%3c of these.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:5 And it shall be, when he shall be guilty in one of these things,%0a%3c that he shall confess that he hath sinned in that thing: 5:6 And he%0a%3c shall bring his trespass offering unto the LORD for his sin which he%0a%3c hath sinned, a female from the flock, a lamb or a kid of the goats,%0a%3c for a sin offering; and the priest shall make an atonement for him%0a%3c concerning his sin.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:7 And if he be not able to bring a lamb, then he shall bring for his%0a%3c trespass, which he hath committed, two turtledoves, or two young%0a%3c pigeons, unto the LORD; one for a sin offering, and the other for a%0a%3c burnt offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 5:8 And he shall bring them unto the priest, who shall offer that%0a%3c which is for the sin offering first, and wring off his head from his%0a%3c neck, but shall not divide it asunder: 5:9 And he shall sprinkle of%0a%3c the blood of the sin offering upon the side of the altar; and the rest%0a%3c of the blood shall be wrung out at th