od of%0a%3c her purifying threescore and six days.%0a%3c %0a%3c 12:6 And when the days of her purifying are fulfilled, for a son, or%0a%3c for a daughter, she shall bring a lamb of the first year for a burnt%0a%3c offering, and a young pigeon, or a turtledove, for a sin offering,%0a%3c unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, unto the priest:%0a%3c 12:7 Who shall offer it before the LORD, and make an atonement for%0a%3c her; and she shall be cleansed from the issue of her blood. This is%0a%3c the law for her that hath born a male or a female.%0a%3c %0a%3c 12:8 And if she be not able to bring a lamb, then she shall bring two%0a%3c turtles, or two young pigeons; the one for the burnt offering, and the%0a%3c other for a sin offering: and the priest shall make an atonement for%0a%3c her, and she shall be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron, saying, 13:2 When a man%0a%3c shall have in the skin of his flesh a rising, a scab, or bright spot,%0a%3c and it be in the skin of his flesh like the plague of leprosy; then he%0a%3c shall be brought unto Aaron the priest, or unto one of his sons the%0a%3c priests: 13:3 And the priest shall look on the plague in the skin of%0a%3c the flesh: and when the hair in the plague is turned white, and the%0a%3c plague in sight be deeper than the skin of his flesh, it is a plague%0a%3c of leprosy: and the priest shall look on him, and pronounce him%0a%3c unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:4 If the bright spot be white in the skin of his flesh, and in%0a%3c sight be not deeper than the skin, and the hair thereof be not turned%0a%3c white; then the priest shall shut up him that hath the plague seven%0a%3c days: 13:5 And the priest shall look on him the seventh day: and,%0a%3c behold, if the plague in his sight be at a stay, and the plague spread%0a%3c not in the skin; then the priest shall shut him up seven days more:%0a%3c 13:6 And the priest shall look on him again the seventh day: and,%0a%3c behold, if the plague be somewhat dark, and the plague spread not in%0a%3c the skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean: it is but a scab: and%0a%3c he shall wash his clothes, and be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:7 But if the scab spread much abroad in the skin, after that he%0a%3c hath been seen of the priest for his cleansing, he shall be seen of%0a%3c the priest again.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:8 And if the priest see that, behold, the scab spreadeth in the%0a%3c skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a leprosy.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:9 When the plague of leprosy is in a man, then he shall be brought%0a%3c unto the priest; 13:10 And the priest shall see him: and, behold, if%0a%3c the rising be white in the skin, and it have turned the hair white,%0a%3c and there be quick raw flesh in the rising; 13:11 It is an old leprosy%0a%3c in the skin of his flesh, and the priest shall pronounce him unclean,%0a%3c and shall not shut him up: for he is unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:12 And if a leprosy break out abroad in the skin, and the leprosy%0a%3c cover all the skin of him that hath the plague from his head even to%0a%3c his foot, wheresoever the priest looketh; 13:13 Then the priest shall%0a%3c consider: and, behold, if the leprosy have covered all his flesh, he%0a%3c shall pronounce him clean that hath the plague: it is all turned%0a%3c white: he is clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:14 But when raw flesh appeareth in him, he shall be unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:15 And the priest shall see the raw flesh, and pronounce him to be%0a%3c unclean: for the raw flesh is unclean: it is a leprosy.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:16 Or if the raw flesh turn again, and be changed unto white, he%0a%3c shall come unto the priest; 13:17 And the priest shall see him: and,%0a%3c behold, if the plague be turned into white; then the priest shall%0a%3c pronounce him clean that hath the plague: he is clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:18 The flesh also, in which, even in the skin thereof, was a boil,%0a%3c and is healed, 13:19 And in the place of the boil there be a white%0a%3c rising, or a bright spot, white, and somewhat reddish, and it be%0a%3c shewed to the priest; 13:20 And if, when the priest seeth it, behold,%0a%3c it be in sight lower than the skin, and the hair thereof be turned%0a%3c white; the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a plague of%0a%3c leprosy broken out of the boil.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:21 But if the priest look on it, and, behold, there be no white%0a%3c hairs therein, and if it be not lower than the skin, but be somewhat%0a%3c dark; then the priest shall shut him up seven days: 13:22 And if it%0a%3c spread much abroad in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him%0a%3c unclean: it is a plague.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:23 But if the bright spot stay in his place, and spread not, it is%0a%3c a burning boil; and the priest shall pronounce him clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:24 Or if there be any flesh, in the skin whereof there is a hot%0a%3c burning, and the quick flesh that burneth have a white bright spot,%0a%3c somewhat reddish, or white; 13:25 Then the priest shall look upon it:%0a%3c and, behold, if the hair in the bright spot be turned white, and it be%0a%3c in sight deeper than the skin; it is a leprosy broken out of the%0a%3c burning: wherefore the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is the%0a%3c plague of leprosy.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:26 But if the priest look on it, and, behold, there be no white%0a%3c hair in the bright spot, and it be no lower than the other skin, but%0a%3c be somewhat dark; then the priest shall shut him up seven days: 13:27%0a%3c And the priest shall look upon him the seventh day: and if it be%0a%3c spread much abroad in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him%0a%3c unclean: it is the plague of leprosy.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:28 And if the bright spot stay in his place, and spread not in the%0a%3c skin, but it be somewhat dark; it is a rising of the burning, and the%0a%3c priest shall pronounce him clean: for it is an inflammation of the%0a%3c burning.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:29 If a man or woman have a plague upon the head or the beard;%0a%3c 13:30 Then the priest shall see the plague: and, behold, if it be in%0a%3c sight deeper than the skin; and there be in it a yellow thin hair;%0a%3c then the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a dry scall, even a%0a%3c leprosy upon the head or beard.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:31 And if the priest look on the plague of the scall, and, behold,%0a%3c it be not in sight deeper than the skin, and that there is no black%0a%3c hair in it; then the priest shall shut up him that hath the plague of%0a%3c the scall seven days: 13:32 And in the seventh day the priest shall%0a%3c look on the plague: and, behold, if the scall spread not, and there be%0a%3c in it no yellow hair, and the scall be not in sight deeper than the%0a%3c skin; 13:33 He shall be shaven, but the scall shall he not shave; and%0a%3c the priest shall shut up him that hath the scall seven days more:%0a%3c 13:34 And in the seventh day the priest shall look on the scall: and,%0a%3c behold, if the scall be not spread in the skin, nor be in sight deeper%0a%3c than the skin; then the priest shall pronounce him clean: and he shall%0a%3c wash his clothes, and be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:35 But if the scall spread much in the skin after his cleansing;%0a%3c 13:36 Then the priest shall look on him: and, behold, if the scall be%0a%3c spread in the skin, the priest shall not seek for yellow hair; he is%0a%3c unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:37 But if the scall be in his sight at a stay, and that there is%0a%3c black hair grown up therein; the scall is healed, he is clean: and the%0a%3c priest shall pronounce him clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:38 If a man also or a woman have in the skin of their flesh bright%0a%3c spots, even white bright spots; 13:39 Then the priest shall look: and,%0a%3c behold, if the bright spots in the skin of their flesh be darkish%0a%3c white; it is a freckled spot that groweth in the skin; he is clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:40 And the man whose hair is fallen off his head,