or in linen, or any thing of skin, wherein the plague is: for%0a%3c it is a fretting leprosy; it shall be burnt in the fire.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:53 And if the priest shall look, and, behold, the plague be not%0a%3c spread in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any%0a%3c thing of skin; 13:54 Then the priest shall command that they wash the%0a%3c thing wherein the plague is, and he shall shut it up seven days more:%0a%3c 13:55 And the priest shall look on the plague, after that it is%0a%3c washed: and, behold, if the plague have not changed his colour, and%0a%3c the plague be not spread; it is unclean; thou shalt burn it in the%0a%3c fire; it is fret inward, whether it be bare within or without.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:56 And if the priest look, and, behold, the plague be somewhat dark%0a%3c after the washing of it; then he shall rend it out of the garment, or%0a%3c out of the skin, or out of the warp, or out of the woof: 13:57 And if%0a%3c it appear still in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or%0a%3c in any thing of skin; it is a spreading plague: thou shalt burn that%0a%3c wherein the plague is with fire.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:58 And the garment, either warp, or woof, or whatsoever thing of%0a%3c skin it be, which thou shalt wash, if the plague be departed from%0a%3c them, then it shall be washed the second time, and shall be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 13:59 This is the law of the plague of leprosy in a garment of woollen%0a%3c or linen, either in the warp, or woof, or any thing of skins, to%0a%3c pronounce it clean, or to pronounce it unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:1 And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying, 14:2 This shall be the law%0a%3c of the leper in the day of his cleansing: He shall be brought unto the%0a%3c priest: 14:3 And the priest shall go forth out of the camp; and the%0a%3c priest shall look, and, behold, if the plague of leprosy be healed in%0a%3c the leper; 14:4 Then shall the priest command to take for him that is%0a%3c to be cleansed two birds alive and clean, and cedar wood, and scarlet,%0a%3c and hyssop: 14:5 And the priest shall command that one of the birds be%0a%3c killed in an earthen vessel over running water: 14:6 As for the living%0a%3c bird, he shall take it, and the cedar wood, and the scarlet, and the%0a%3c hyssop, and shall dip them and the living bird in the blood of the%0a%3c bird that was killed over the running water: 14:7 And he shall%0a%3c sprinkle upon him that is to be cleansed from the leprosy seven times,%0a%3c and shall pronounce him clean, and shall let the living bird loose%0a%3c into the open field.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:8 And he that is to be cleansed shall wash his clothes, and shave%0a%3c off all his hair, and wash himself in water, that he may be clean: and%0a%3c after that he shall come into the camp, and shall tarry abroad out of%0a%3c his tent seven days.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:9 But it shall be on the seventh day, that he shall shave all his%0a%3c hair off his head and his beard and his eyebrows, even all his hair he%0a%3c shall shave off: and he shall wash his clothes, also he shall wash his%0a%3c flesh in water, and he shall be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:10 And on the eighth day he shall take two he lambs without%0a%3c blemish, and one ewe lamb of the first year without blemish, and three%0a%3c tenth deals of fine flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and%0a%3c one log of oil.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:11 And the priest that maketh him clean shall present the man that%0a%3c is to be made clean, and those things, before the LORD, at the door of%0a%3c the tabernacle of the congregation: 14:12 And the priest shall take%0a%3c one he lamb, and offer him for a trespass offering, and the log of%0a%3c oil, and wave them for a wave offering before the LORD: 14:13 And he%0a%3c shall slay the lamb in the place where he shall kill the sin offering%0a%3c and the burnt offering, in the holy place: for as the sin offering is%0a%3c the priest's, so is the trespass offering: it is most holy: 14:14 And%0a%3c the priest shall take some of the blood of the trespass offering, and%0a%3c the priest shall put it upon the tip of the right ear of him that is%0a%3c to be cleansed, and upon the thumb of his right hand, and upon the%0a%3c great toe of his right foot: 14:15 And the priest shall take some of%0a%3c the log of oil, and pour it into the palm of his own left hand: 14:16%0a%3c And the priest shall dip his right finger in the oil that is in his%0a%3c left hand, and shall sprinkle of the oil with his finger seven times%0a%3c before the LORD: 14:17 And of the rest of the oil that is in his hand%0a%3c shall the priest put upon the tip of the right ear of him that is to%0a%3c be cleansed, and upon the thumb of his right hand, and upon the great%0a%3c toe of his right foot, upon the blood of the trespass offering: 14:18%0a%3c And the remnant of the oil that is in the priest's hand he shall pour%0a%3c upon the head of him that is to be cleansed: and the priest shall make%0a%3c an atonement for him before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:19 And the priest shall offer the sin offering, and make an%0a%3c atonement for him that is to be cleansed from his uncleanness; and%0a%3c afterward he shall kill the burnt offering: 14:20 And the priest shall%0a%3c offer the burnt offering and the meat offering upon the altar: and the%0a%3c priest shall make an atonement for him, and he shall be clean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:21 And if he be poor, and cannot get so much; then he shall take%0a%3c one lamb for a trespass offering to be waved, to make an atonement for%0a%3c him, and one tenth deal of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat%0a%3c offering, and a log of oil; 14:22 And two turtledoves, or two young%0a%3c pigeons, such as he is able to get; and the one shall be a sin%0a%3c offering, and the other a burnt offering.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:23 And he shall bring them on the eighth day for his cleansing unto%0a%3c the priest, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation,%0a%3c before the LORD.%0a%3c %0a%