o me there is as it were a plague%0a%3c in the house: 14:36 Then the priest shall command that they empty the%0a%3c house, before the priest go into it to see the plague, that all that%0a%3c is in the house be not made unclean: and afterward the priest shall go%0a%3c in to see the house: 14:37 And he shall look on the plague, and,%0a%3c behold, if the plague be in the walls of the house with hollow%0a%3c strakes, greenish or reddish, which in sight are lower than the wall;%0a%3c 14:38 Then the priest shall go out of the house to the door of the%0a%3c house, and shut up the house seven days: 14:39 And the priest shall%0a%3c come again the seventh day, and shall look: and, behold, if the plague%0a%3c be spread in the walls of the house; 14:40 Then the priest shall%0a%3c command that they take away the stones in which the plague is, and%0a%3c they shall cast them into an unclean place without the city: 14:41 And%0a%3c he shall cause the house to be scraped within round about, and they%0a%3c shall pour out the dust that they scrape off without the city into an%0a%3c unclean place: 14:42 And they shall take other stones, and put them in%0a%3c the place of those stones; and he shall take other morter, and shall%0a%3c plaister the house.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:43 And if the plague come again, and break out in the house, after%0a%3c that he hath taken away the stones, and after he hath scraped the%0a%3c house, and after it is plaistered; 14:44 Then the priest shall come%0a%3c and look, and, behold, if the plague be spread in the house, it is a%0a%3c fretting leprosy in the house; it is unclean.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:45 And he shall break down the house, the stones of it, and the%0a%3c timber thereof, and all the morter of the house; and he shall carry%0a%3c them forth out of the city into an unclean place.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:46 Moreover he that goeth into the house all the while that it is%0a%3c shut up shall be unclean until the even.%0a%3c %0a%3c 14:47 And he that lieth in the house shal